#: aab123c91fce4256a04ff63a35cef12d of tensormesh.mesh.mesh.Mesh:1
msgid ""
"FEM mesh — interpolation-node coordinates, per-element-type connectivity,"
" and point/cell/field data attached to either. Mixed-element meshes are "
"supported via :attr:`cells` being a :class:`~tensormesh.nn.BufferDict` "
"keyed by element type string (e.g. ``\"triangle\"``, ``\"quad\"``, "
"``\"tetra\"``)."
msgstr ""

#: 6c4647878a44421c84d27e32bcaf8f17 of tensormesh.mesh.mesh.Mesh:7
msgid ""
"A \"point\" throughout the API means an interpolation node / degree of "
"freedom — for ``order=1`` this is the corner vertex of an element, for "
"``order>=2`` it also includes mid-edge, mid-face, and interior nodes."
msgstr ""

